summary: TL*THE CONTACT OWNS A 1988 BUICK REGAL.  WHILE DRIVING AT AN UNKNOWN SPEED, THE VEHICLE STRUCK A GUARDRAIL AND WAS DESTROYED.  THE CONTACT SUSTAINED NECK INJURIES AND A POLICE REPORT WAS FILED.  SHE THOUGHT THE VEHICLE HAD ANTILOCK BRAKES, BUT REALIZED IT DID NOT AFTER THE CRASH OCCURRED.  THE CONTACT STATED THAT THE MANUFACTURER SHOULD HAVE A PERMANENT LABEL TO INDICATE THAT THE VEHICLE HAS ANTILOCK BRAKES SINCE IT IS AN OPTIONAL FEATURE.  SHE FURTHER STATED THAT IT COULD CAUSE NUMEROUS FATAL CRASHES BECAUSE THE BRAKES HAVE TO BE APPLIED A CERTAIN WAY DEPENDING ON THE ANTILOCK BRAKE SYSTEM.  THE DEALER INFORMED HER THAT SHE HAD ANTILOCK BRAKES.  THE VIN WAS UNKNOWN.  THE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS 60,000.

TL*THE CONTACT OWNS A 1988 BUICK REGAL.  THE VEHICLE WAS TAKEN TO BE INSPECTED AND THE CONTACT WAS INFORMED THAT THE REAR FRAME WAS ROTTED.  SHE WAS FURTHER INFORMED NOT TO DRIVE THE VEHICLE.  THE CURRENT AND FAILURE MILEAGES WERE 49,600.

summary: TL*- THE CONTACT OWNS A 1988 BUICK REGAL WHICH SHE PURCHASED RECENTLY.  THE ODOMETER ON THE VEHICLE DID NOT WORK.  THE CONTACT CLAIMED THAT THE DEALER DID NOT  INSPECT THE VEHICLES BEFORE THEY SOLD THEM.  THEY REPAIRED THE REAR BRAKES, AND THE DRIVER'S SIDE FRONT BRAKES, BUT THE BRAKES  WERE STILL NOT OPERATING PROPERLY.  THE VEHICLE COULD NOT PASS AN INSPECTION, AND NOW THE VEHICLE DID NOT START.  THE MECHANIC BELIEVED THAT THE FAILURE MAY BE IN THE FUEL FILTER, FUEL PUMP OR SOMETHING ELSE.    THE VEHICLE WOULD TURN OVER, BUT WOULD NOT START.  WHEN SHE TRIED TO TURN ON THE IGNITION SHE COULD SMELL GAS FUMES.  THE WIRING WAS CUT BY THE PREVIOUS OWNER AND THE POWER LOCKS DID NOT WORK.  THE DEALER REFUSED TO GIVE THE CONTACT THE RECEIPT FOR PARTS PURCHASED TO REPAIR THE BRAKES, AND REFUSED TO MAKE ANY FURTHER REPAIRS ON THE VEHICLE.  THE CURRENT AND FAILURE MILEAGE WERE 155,925 . *AK
